sentences.english: Venezuelan politics have been very complicated lately.
sentences.chinese: 委內瑞拉的政治最近很紛雜。

sentences.english: I don't want to describe how I have failed in this intricate world .
sentences.chinese: 我不想去描述在這個紛雜的世界裏我如何失敗了。

sentences.english: He said he is now dealing with mixed emotions.
sentences.chinese: 他說他現在還在處理自己紛雜的情緒。

sentences.english: But eventually the complexities of the human world would intrude.
sentences.chinese: 但最終紛雜的人類社會會侵入這裏的。

definition: lit. to dispel the clouds and see the sun (idiom); fig. to restore justice
(of a person) sad beyond words (idiom)/(of music, literature etc) poignant/very sentimental
to mention sth without elaborating (idiom); not giving details
properly/satisfactorily/firmly/very fitting/appropriate/proper/to be in good order/also written 妥帖
lit. dragons and snakes mingle (idiom)/fig. a mix of good people and scumbags
lit. one body two sides (idiom)/fig. a situation with two sides to it
lit. draw legs on a snake (idiom); fig. to ruin the effect by adding sth superfluous/to overdo it
different routes to the same destination (idiom); fig. different means of achieve the same end
